Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.83,0:00:03.24,English1,,0,0,0,,The cosmos is all there is
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.58,0:00:04.78,English1,,0,0,0,,or ever was,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.28,0:00:06.31,English1,,0,0,0,,or ever will be
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.73,0:00:09.06,English1,,0,0,0,,Come with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.53,0:00:12.50,English1,,0,0,0,,A generation ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.54,0:00:14.90,English1,,0,0,0,,the astronomer Carl Sagan stood here
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.94,0:00:16.91,English1,,0,0,0,,and launched hundreds of millions of us
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.94,0:00:18.91,English1,,0,0,0,,on a great adventure...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.94,0:00:22.74,English1,,0,0,0,,the exploration of the universe revealed by science.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.78,0:00:25.75,English1,,0,0,0,,It's time to get going again.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.78,0:00:28.75,English1,,0,0,0,,We're about to begin a journey that will take us
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.79,0:00:31.85,English1,,0,0,0,,from the infinitesimal to the infinite,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.89,0:00:34.86,English1,,0,0,0,,from the dawn of time to the distant future.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.89,0:00:39.19,English1,,0,0,0,,We'll explore galaxies and suns and worlds,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.23,0:00:42.23,English1,,0,0,0,,surf the gravity waves of space-time,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.27,0:00:45.60,English1,,0,0,0,,encounter beings that live in fire and ice,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.64,0:00:49.37,English1,,0,0,0,,explore the planets of stars that never die,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.41,0:00:51.97,English1,,0,0,0,,discover atoms as massive as suns
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.01,0:00:56.08,English1,,0,0,0,,and universes smaller than atoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.11,0:00:59.25,English1,,0,0,0,,Cosmos{\i1} is also a story about us.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.28,0:01:03.42,English1,,0,0,0,,It's the saga of how wandering\N{\i1}bands of hunters and gatherers
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.45,0:01:08.12,English1,,0,0,0,,found their way to the stars,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.16,0:01:11.93,English1,,0,0,0,,one adventure with many heroes.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.64,0:01:24.11,English1,,0,0,0,,To make this journey,we'll need imagination.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.14,0:01:26.44,English1,,0,0,0,,But imagination alone is not enough
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.48,0:01:29.65,English1,,0,0,0,,because the reality of nature is far more wondrous
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.68,0:01:32.01,English1,,0,0,0,,than anything we can imagine.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.05,0:01:39.69,English1,,0,0,0,,This adventure is made possible\Nby generations of searchers
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.72,0:01:43.19,English1,,0,0,0,,strictly adhering to a simple set of rules...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.23,0:01:47.03,English1,,0,0,0,,test ideas by experiment and observation,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.06,0:01:49.97,English1,,0,0,0,,build on those ideas\Nthat pass the test,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.00,0:01:52.20,English1,,0,0,0,,reject the ones that fail,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.24,0:01:54.84,English1,,0,0,0,,follow the evidence wherever it leads
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.87,0:01:57.51,English1,,0,0,0,,and question everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.54,0:02:00.01,English1,,0,0,0,,Accept these terms,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.04,0:02:03.98,English1,,0,0,0,,and the cosmos is yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.01,0:02:07.32,English1,,0,0,0,,Now come with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.30,0:04:04.30,English1,,0,0,0,,In this ship of the Imagination,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.30,0:04:06.90,English1,,0,0,0,,free from the shackles of space and time,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.94,0:04:09.97,English1,,0,0,0,,we can go anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.01,0:04:12.24,English1,,0,0,0,,If you want to see where we are in space,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.28,0:04:15.44,English1,,0,0,0,,just look out the front window.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.38,0:04:23.02,English1,,0,0,0,,In the dimension of time, the past lies beneath us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.32,0:04:29.53,English1,,0,0,0,,Here's what Earth looked like 250 million years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.13,0:04:35.70,English1,,0,0,0,,If you want to see the future, look up.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.73,0:04:41.00,English1,,0,0,0,,And this is how it could appear 250 million years from now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.37,0:04:43.81,English1,,0,0,0,,If we're going to be venturing out
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.84,0:04:46.68,English1,,0,0,0,,into the farthest reaches of the cosmos,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.71,0:04:49.61,English1,,0,0,0,,we need to know our{\i1} cosmic{\i} address,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.65,0:04:53.35,English1,,0,0,0,,and this is the first line of that address.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.54,0:05:18.91,English1,,0,0,0,,We're leaving the Earth,\N{\i1}the only home we've ever known,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.94,0:05:23.35,English1,,0,0,0,,for the farthest reaches of the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.38,0:05:31.25,English1,,0,0,0,,Our nearest neighbor, the Moon, has no sky,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.29,0:05:34.69,English1,,0,0,0,,no ocean, no life...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.72,0:05:38.09,English1,,0,0,0,,just the scars of cosmic impacts.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.11,0:05:54.08,English1,,0,0,0,,Our star powers the wind and the waves
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.11,0:05:57.91,English1,,0,0,0,,and all the life on the surface of our world.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.95,0:06:00.52,English1,,0,0,0,,The Sun holds all the worlds of the solar system
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.55,0:06:05.09,English1,,0,0,0,,in its gravitational embrace, starting with Mercury...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.64,0:06:27.54,English1,,0,0,0,,...to cloud-covered Venus,\N{\i1}where runaway greenhouse effect
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.58,0:06:31.18,English1,,0,0,0,,has turned it into a kind of hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.12,0:06:38.92,English1,,0,0,0,,Mars...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.96,0:06:43.93,English1,,0,0,0,,a world with as much land as Earth itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.14,0:06:59.44,English1,,0,0,0,,A belt of rocky asteroids circles the Sun
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.48,0:07:01.94,English1,,0,0,0,,between the orbits of Mars and Jupiter.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.46,0:07:17.76,English1,,0,0,0,,With its four giant moons\N{\i1}and dozens of smaller ones,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.79,0:07:21.26,English1,,0,0,0,,Jupiter is like its own little solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.30,0:07:25.70,English1,,0,0,0,,It has more mass than\Nall the other planets combined.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.35,0:07:39.32,English1,,0,0,0,,Jupiter's Great Red Spot...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.35,0:07:42.48,English1,,0,0,0,,a hurricane three times the size of our whole planet
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.52,0:07:46.16,English1,,0,0,0,,that's been raging for centuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.51,0:08:10.38,English1,,0,0,0,,The crown jewel of our solar system, Saturn,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.41,0:08:13.65,English1,,0,0,0,,ringed by freeways of countless orbiting
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.68,0:08:16.05,English1,,0,0,0,,and slowly tumbling snowballs...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.09,0:08:20.09,English1,,0,0,0,,every snowball, a little moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.72,0:08:53.89,English1,,0,0,0,,Uranus...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.92,0:08:55.89,English1,,0,0,0,,and Neptune,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.93,0:09:00.23,English1,,0,0,0,,the outermost planets,\N{\i1}unknown to the ancients
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.26,0:09:05.30,English1,,0,0,0,,and only discovered after\N{\i1}the invention of the telescope.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.44,0:09:08.80,English1,,0,0,0,,Beyond the outermost planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.84,0:09:13.51,English1,,0,0,0,,there's a swarm of tens\N{\i1}of thousands of frozen worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.03,0:09:33.66,English1,,0,0,0,,And Pluto is one them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.34,0:09:48.74,English1,,0,0,0,,Of all our spacecraft,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.78,0:09:52.08,English1,,0,0,0,,this is the one that's traveled\N{\i1}farthest from home...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.12,0:09:55.32,English1,,0,0,0,,Voyager 1.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.35,0:09:59.99,English1,,0,0,0,,She bears a message to\Na billion years from now,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.02,0:10:02.76,English1,,0,0,0,,something of who we were,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.79,0:10:04.93,English1,,0,0,0,,how we felt
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.96,0:10:06.93,English1,,0,0,0,,and the music we made.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.18,0:10:20.01,English1,,0,0,0,,The deeper waters
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.04,0:10:21.88,English1,,0,0,0,,of this vast cosmic ocean
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.91,0:10:25.71,English1,,0,0,0,,and their numberless worlds lie ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.64,0:10:41.51,English1,,0,0,0,,From out here, the Sun may look like\Njust another star.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.54,0:10:43.94,English1,,0,0,0,,But it still exerts its gravitational hold
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.98,0:10:46.34,English1,,0,0,0,,on a trillion frozen comets,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.38,0:10:49.11,English1,,0,0,0,,leftovers from the formation of the solar system
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.15,0:10:51.95,English1,,0,0,0,,nearly five billion years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.98,0:10:54.59,English1,,0,0,0,,It's called the Oort Cloud.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.62,0:10:57.32,English1,,0,0,0,,No one has ever seen it before,\N{\i1}nor could they,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.36,0:10:59.59,English1,,0,0,0,,because each one of these little worlds
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.63,0:11:01.83,English1,,0,0,0,,is as far from its nearest neighbor
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.86,0:11:05.46,English1,,0,0,0,,as Earth is from Saturn.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.50,0:11:09.30,English1,,0,0,0,,This enormous cloud of comets\Nencloses the solar system,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.33,0:11:13.14,English1,,0,0,0,,which is the second line\Nof our cosmic address.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.04,0:11:21.68,English1,,0,0,0,,We've only been able to detect\N{\i1}the planets of other stars
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.71,0:11:23.68,English1,,0,0,0,,for a few decades,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.72,0:11:27.45,English1,,0,0,0,,but we already know\N{\i1}that planets are plentiful...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.49,0:11:30.12,English1,,0,0,0,,they outnumber the stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.16,0:11:33.56,English1,,0,0,0,,Almost all of them will be very different from Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.59,0:11:36.06,English1,,0,0,0,,and hostile to life as we know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.09,0:11:38.46,English1,,0,0,0,,But what do we know about life?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.50,0:11:41.53,English1,,0,0,0,,We've met only one kind so far.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.57,0:11:43.50,English1,,0,0,0,,Earthlife.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.54,0:11:44.84,English1,,0,0,0,,See anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.87,0:11:46.84,English1,,0,0,0,,Just empty space, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.87,0:11:49.64,English1,,0,0,0,,Human eyes see only a sliver of the light
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.68,0:11:51.64,English1,,0,0,0,,that shines in the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.68,0:11:55.88,English1,,0,0,0,,But science gives us the power\Nto see what our senses cannot.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.91,0:11:58.65,English1,,0,0,0,,Infrared is the kind of light made visible
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.68,0:12:00.69,English1,,0,0,0,,by night-vision goggles.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.72,0:12:03.35,English1,,0,0,0,,Throw an infrared sensor across the darkness...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.79,0:12:06.39,English1,,0,0,0,,Rogue planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.43,0:12:08.69,English1,,0,0,0,,World without a sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.60,0:12:15.03,English1,,0,0,0,,Our galaxy has billions of them,\Nadrift in perpetual night.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.07,0:12:18.60,English1,,0,0,0,,They're orphans, cast away\Nfrom their mother stars
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.64,0:12:22.07,English1,,0,0,0,,during the chaotic birth\Nof their native star systems.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.81,0:12:26.44,English1,,0,0,0,,Rogue planets are molten at the core
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.48,0:12:28.45,English1,,0,0,0,,but frozen at the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.48,0:12:30.45,English1,,0,0,0,,There may be oceans of liquid water
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.48,0:12:33.48,English1,,0,0,0,,in the zone between those extremes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.06,0:12:41.66,English1,,0,0,0,,Who knows what might be swimming there?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.43,0:12:49.60,English1,,0,0,0,,This is what the Milky Way\Nlooks like in infrared.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.64,0:12:52.70,English1,,0,0,0,,Every single dot,\Nnot just the bright ones,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.74,0:12:54.91,English1,,0,0,0,,is a star.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.94,0:12:56.91,English1,,0,0,0,,How many stars?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.94,0:12:58.91,English1,,0,0,0,,How many worlds?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.94,0:13:01.41,English1,,0,0,0,,How many ways of being alive?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.45,0:13:04.42,English1,,0,0,0,,Where are we{\i1} in this picture?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.45,0:13:06.88,English1,,0,0,0,,See that trailing outer arm?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.92,0:13:09.09,English1,,0,0,0,,That's where we live...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.12,0:13:12.32,English1,,0,0,0,,about 30,000 light-years\N{\i1}from the center.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.36,0:13:14.06,English1,,0,0,0,,The Milky Way Galaxy
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.09,0:13:17.40,English1,,0,0,0,,is the next line of our cosmic address.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.43,0:13:19.80,English1,,0,0,0,,We're now a hundred thousand\N{\i1}light-years from home.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.83,0:13:23.07,English1,,0,0,0,,It would take light,\N{\i1}the fastest thing there is,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.10,0:13:26.97,English1,,0,0,0,,a hundred thousand years\N{\i1}to reach us from Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.71,0:13:32.11,English1,,0,0,0,,This is the Great Spiral in Andromeda,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.14,0:13:34.11,English1,,0,0,0,,the galaxy next door.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.15,0:13:36.11,English1,,0,0,0,,We call our two giant galaxies
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.15,0:13:38.12,English1,,0,0,0,,and a smattering of smaller ones
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.15,0:13:40.49,English1,,0,0,0,,the "local group."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.16,0:13:51.46,English1,,0,0,0,,Can't even find our home galaxy from out here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.50,0:13:55.70,English1,,0,0,0,,It's just one of thousands\N{\i1}in the Virgo Supercluster.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.73,0:13:57.64,English1,,0,0,0,,On this scale,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.67,0:14:01.27,English1,,0,0,0,,all the objects we see,\Nincluding the tiniest dots,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.31,0:14:03.11,English1,,0,0,0,,are galaxies.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.14,0:14:05.68,English1,,0,0,0,,Each galaxy contains billions of suns
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.71,0:14:07.78,English1,,0,0,0,,and countless worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.81,0:14:11.45,English1,,0,0,0,,Yet, the entire Virgo Supercluster itself
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.48,0:14:14.69,English1,,0,0,0,,forms but a tiny part of our universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.39,0:14:20.36,English1,,0,0,0,,This is the cosmos\N{\i1}on the grandest scale we know...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.39,0:14:23.69,English1,,0,0,0,,a network of a hundred billion galaxies.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.73,0:14:27.17,English1,,0,0,0,,It's the last line of our cosmic address...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.20,0:14:29.20,English1,,0,0,0,,for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.77,0:14:32.24,English1,,0,0,0,,Observable universe?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.27,0:14:34.14,English1,,0,0,0,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.17,0:14:36.91,English1,,0,0,0,,Even for us, in our\NShip of the Imagination,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.94,0:14:40.55,English1,,0,0,0,,there's a limit to how far\Nwe can see in space-time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.58,0:14:42.98,English1,,0,0,0,,It's our cosmic horizon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.02,0:14:46.08,English1,,0,0,0,,Beyond that horizon\Nlie parts of the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.12,0:14:48.25,English1,,0,0,0,,that are too far away.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.29,0:14:50.25,English1,,0,0,0,,There hasn't been enough time
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.29,0:14:53.36,English1,,0,0,0,,in the 13.8 billion year history of the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.39,0:14:55.89,English1,,0,0,0,,for their light to have reached us.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.93,0:15:01.33,English1,,0,0,0,,Many of us suspect\N{\i1}that all of this...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.37,0:15:05.57,English1,,0,0,0,,all the worlds, stars,\N{\i1}galaxies and clusters
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.60,0:15:08.01,English1,,0,0,0,,in our observable universe...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.04,0:15:12.74,English1,,0,0,0,,is but one tiny bubble in an infinite ocean
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.78,0:15:14.81,English1,,0,0,0,,of other universes...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.42,0:15:18.88,English1,,0,0,0,,...a multiverse.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.92,0:15:22.69,English1,,0,0,0,,Universe upon universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.72,0:15:25.29,English1,,0,0,0,,Worlds without end.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.00,0:15:32.06,English1,,0,0,0,,Feeling a little small?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.10,0:15:35.57,English1,,0,0,0,,Well, in the context\Nof the cosmos, we{\i1} are small.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.60,0:15:38.90,English1,,0,0,0,,We may just be little guys\Nliving on a speck of dust,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.94,0:15:41.31,English1,,0,0,0,,afloat in a staggering immensity,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.34,0:15:43.44,English1,,0,0,0,,but we don't think small.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.48,0:15:46.91,English1,,0,0,0,,This cosmic perspective is relatively new.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.95,0:15:51.22,English1,,0,0,0,,A mere four centuries ago,\Nour tiny world was oblivious
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.25,0:15:53.22,English1,,0,0,0,,to the rest of the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.25,0:15:55.22,English1,,0,0,0,,There were no telescopes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.25,0:15:58.99,English1,,0,0,0,,The universe was only what you\Ncould see with the naked eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.02,0:16:01.09,English1,,0,0,0,,Back in 1599,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.13,0:16:04.46,English1,,0,0,0,,everyone knew that the Sun,\Nplanets and stars
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.50,0:16:08.50,English1,,0,0,0,,were just lights in the sky\Nthat revolved around the Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.53,0:16:12.57,English1,,0,0,0,,and that we were the center\N{\i1}of a little universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.60,0:16:15.37,English1,,0,0,0,,a universe made for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.94,0:16:19.31,English1,,0,0,0,,There was only one man\N{\i1}on the whole planet
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.35,0:16:22.18,English1,,0,0,0,,who envisioned\N{\i1}an infinitely grander cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.21,0:16:24.75,English1,,0,0,0,,And how was he{\i1} spending{\i}\N{\i1}New Year's Eve
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.78,0:16:27.92,English1,,0,0,0,,of the year 1600?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.95,0:16:30.79,English1,,0,0,0,,Why, in prison, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.85,0:16:40.02,English1,,0,0,0,,There comes a time in our lives
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.05,0:16:43.29,English1,,0,0,0,,when we first realize we're not\Nthe center of the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.32,0:16:46.52,English1,,0,0,0,,that we belong to something\Nmuch greater than ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.56,0:16:48.53,English1,,0,0,0,,It's part of growing up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.56,0:16:50.80,English1,,0,0,0,,And as it happens to each of us,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.83,0:16:53.13,English1,,0,0,0,,so it began to happen to our civilization
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.17,0:16:55.13,English1,,0,0,0,,in the 16th century.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.17,0:16:57.04,English1,,0,0,0,,Imagine a world before telescopes,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.07,0:16:59.30,English1,,0,0,0,,when the universe\N{\i1}was only what you could see
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.34,0:17:00.84,English1,,0,0,0,,with the naked eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.87,0:17:04.04,English1,,0,0,0,,It was obvious that Earth was motionless,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.08,0:17:05.78,English1,,0,0,0,,and that everything in the heavens...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.81,0:17:08.11,English1,,0,0,0,,the Sun, the Moon, the stars, the planets...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.15,0:17:10.98,English1,,0,0,0,,revolved around us... and then...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.02,0:17:13.28,English1,,0,0,0,,a Polish astronomer and priest named Copernicus
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.32,0:17:17.29,English1,,0,0,0,,made a radical proposal.\NThe Earth was not the center.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.32,0:17:19.79,English1,,0,0,0,,It was just one of the planets,\Nand, like them,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.83,0:17:21.79,English1,,0,0,0,,it revolved around the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.83,0:17:25.13,English1,,0,0,0,,Many, like the Protestant reformer Martin Luther,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.16,0:17:28.13,English1,,0,0,0,,took this idea as a scandalous\Naffront to Scripture.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.17,0:17:30.40,English1,,0,0,0,,They were horrified.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.44,0:17:34.87,English1,,0,0,0,,But for one man,\NCopernicus didn't go far enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.91,0:17:38.01,English1,,0,0,0,,His name was Giordano Bruno,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.04,0:17:40.51,English1,,0,0,0,,and he was a natural-born rebel.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.55,0:17:43.72,English1,,0,0,0,,He longed to bust out of that\N{\i1}cramped little universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.75,0:17:46.18,English1,,0,0,0,,Even as a young Dominican monk in Naples,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.22,0:17:48.39,English1,,0,0,0,,he was a misfit.\N{\i1}This was a time
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.42,0:17:50.72,English1,,0,0,0,,when there was\N{\i1}no freedom of thought in Italy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.76,0:17:52.16,English1,,0,0,0,,But Bruno hungered to know
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.19,0:17:53.99,English1,,0,0,0,,everything about God's creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.03,0:17:56.76,English1,,0,0,0,,He dared to read the books\N{\i1}banned by the Church,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.80,0:17:58.56,English1,,0,0,0,,and that was his undoing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.60,0:18:00.60,English1,,0,0,0,,In one of them,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.63,0:18:04.74,English1,,0,0,0,,an ancient Roman, a man dead\N{\i1}for more than 1,500 years
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.77,0:18:07.71,English1,,0,0,0,,whispered to him of a universe far greater,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.74,0:18:10.74,English1,,0,0,0,,one as boundless as his idea of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.88,0:18:16.85,English1,,0,0,0,,Lucretius asked the reader
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.88,0:18:19.25,English1,,0,0,0,,to imagine standing\N{\i1}at the edge of the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.29,0:18:21.25,English1,,0,0,0,,and shooting an arrow outward.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.29,0:18:23.56,English1,,0,0,0,,If the arrow keeps going,\N{\i1}then clearly,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.59,0:18:26.46,English1,,0,0,0,,the universe extends beyond\N{\i1}what you thought was the edge.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.49,0:18:28.89,English1,,0,0,0,,But if the arrow doesn't keep going...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.93,0:18:31.60,English1,,0,0,0,,say it hits a wall...\N{\i1}then that wall must lie
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.63,0:18:34.57,English1,,0,0,0,,beyond what you thought\N{\i1}was the edge of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.60,0:18:37.90,English1,,0,0,0,,Now if you stand on that{\i1} wall{\i}\N{\i1}and shoot another arrow,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.94,0:18:40.64,English1,,0,0,0,,there are only the same\N{\i1}two possible outcomes...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.67,0:18:43.04,English1,,0,0,0,,it either flies forever out into space,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.08,0:18:45.04,English1,,0,0,0,,or it hits some boundary
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.08,0:18:47.81,English1,,0,0,0,,where you can stand and shoot\N{\i1}yet another arrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.85,0:18:50.42,English1,,0,0,0,,Either way, the universe is unbounded.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.45,0:18:53.72,English1,,0,0,0,,The cosmos must be infinite.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.75,0:18:56.22,English1,,0,0,0,,This made perfect sense to Bruno.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.26,0:18:58.59,English1,,0,0,0,,The God he worshiped was infinite.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.62,0:19:02.46,English1,,0,0,0,,So how, he reasoned, could\N{\i1}Creation be anything less?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.11,0:19:20.95,English1,,0,0,0,,It was the last steady job he ever had.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.36,0:19:32.76,English1,,0,0,0,,And then, when he was 30,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.79,0:19:36.43,English1,,0,0,0,,he had the vision that sealed his fate.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.46,0:19:38.93,English1,,0,0,0,,In this dream, he awakened to a world
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.96,0:19:42.00,English1,,0,0,0,,enclosed inside a confining bowl of stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.03,0:19:45.04,English1,,0,0,0,,This was the cosmos of Bruno's time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.49,0:20:06.02,English1,,0,0,0,,He experienced a sickening moment of fear,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.06,0:20:07.56,English1,,0,0,0,,as if the bottom of everything
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.59,0:20:10.20,English1,,0,0,0,,was falling away beneath his feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.23,0:20:12.70,English1,,0,0,0,,But he summoned up his courage.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.74,0:20:23.54,English1,,0,0,0,,I spread confident wings to space
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.58,0:20:27.15,English1,,0,0,0,,and soared toward the infinite,\N{\i1}leaving far behind me
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.18,0:20:30.52,English1,,0,0,0,,what others strained to see\N{\i1}from a distance.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.55,0:20:33.92,English1,,0,0,0,,Here, there was no up, no down, no edge,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.95,0:20:35.49,English1,,0,0,0,,no center.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.52,0:20:38.92,English1,,0,0,0,,I saw that the Sun\N{\i1}was just another star,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.96,0:20:42.89,English1,,0,0,0,,and the stars were other Suns,\N{\i1}each escorted by other Earths
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.93,0:20:44.53,English1,,0,0,0,,like our own.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.56,0:20:47.83,English1,,0,0,0,,The revelation of this immensity was like
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.87,0:20:49.30,English1,,0,0,0,,falling in love.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.77,0:20:54.74,English1,,0,0,0,,Bruno became an evangelist,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.77,0:20:58.18,English1,,0,0,0,,spreading the gospel\N{\i1}of infinity throughout Europe.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.21,0:21:01.78,English1,,0,0,0,,He assumed that other lovers\N{\i1}of God would naturally embrace
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.81,0:21:04.85,English1,,0,0,0,,this grander and more glorious view of Creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.88,0:21:07.92,English1,,0,0,0,,What a fool I was.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.96,0:21:11.62,English1,,0,0,0,,He was excommunicated
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.66,0:21:13.56,English1,,0,0,0,,by the Roman Catholic Church in his homeland,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.59,0:21:16.03,English1,,0,0,0,,expelled by the Calvinists in Switzerland,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.06,0:21:18.26,English1,,0,0,0,,and by the Lutherans in Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.30,0:21:21.30,English1,,0,0,0,,Bruno jumped at an invitation
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.33,0:21:24.17,English1,,0,0,0,,to lecture at Oxford, in England.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.57,0:21:27.41,English1,,0,0,0,,At last, he thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.44,0:21:31.08,English1,,0,0,0,,a chance to share his vision\N{\i1}with an audience of his peers.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.18,0:21:38.25,English1,,0,0,0,,I have come to present\Na new vision of the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.28,0:21:41.32,English1,,0,0,0,,Copernicus was right to argue that our world
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.35,0:21:43.05,English1,,0,0,0,,is{\i1} not{\i} the center of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.09,0:21:45.12,English1,,0,0,0,,The Earth goes around the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.16,0:21:47.63,English1,,0,0,0,,It's a planet, just like the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.66,0:21:49.73,English1,,0,0,0,,But Copernicus was only the dawn.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.76,0:21:51.93,English1,,0,0,0,,I bring you the sunrise.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.33,0:21:55.40,English1,,0,0,0,,The stars are other fiery suns,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.43,0:21:57.64,English1,,0,0,0,,made of the same substance as the Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.67,0:22:00.67,English1,,0,0,0,,and they have their own watery earths,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.71,0:22:03.78,English1,,0,0,0,,with plants and animals\Nno less noble than our own.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.81,0:22:06.08,English1,,0,0,0,,Are you mad or merely ignorant?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.11,0:22:07.85,English1,,0,0,0,,Everyone knows there is only one world.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.88,0:22:10.35,English1,,0,0,0,,What everyone knows is wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.38,0:22:13.35,English1,,0,0,0,,Our infinite God has created\Na boundless universe
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.39,0:22:15.25,English1,,0,0,0,,with an infinite number of worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.29,0:22:17.29,English1,,0,0,0,,Do they not read Aristotle where you come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.32,0:22:19.02,English1,,0,0,0,,Or even the Bible?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.06,0:22:23.66,English1,,0,0,0,,I beg you, reject antiquity, tradition, faith, and authority.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.70,0:22:24.96,English1,,0,0,0,,Let us begin anew,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.00,0:22:27.00,English1,,0,0,0,,by doubting everything we assume
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.03,0:22:28.13,English1,,0,0,0,,- has been proven.\N- Heretic!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.17,0:22:29.20,English1,,0,0,0,,Infidel!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.24,0:22:31.10,English1,,0,0,0,,Your God is too small.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.68,0:22:39.04,English1,,0,0,0,,A wiser man would have learned his lesson.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.08,0:22:42.38,English1,,0,0,0,,But Bruno was not such a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.42,0:22:46.65,English1,,0,0,0,,He couldn't keep his soaring\Nvision of the cosmos to himself,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.69,0:22:49.62,English1,,0,0,0,,despite the fact that the penalty for doing so
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.66,0:22:52.66,English1,,0,0,0,,in his world was the most vicious form
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.69,0:22:54.69,English1,,0,0,0,,of cruel and unusual punishment.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.80,0:23:01.47,English1,,0,0,0,,Giordano Bruno lived at a time when there was no such thing
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.50,0:23:03.44,English1,,0,0,0,,as the separation of church and state,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.47,0:23:06.00,English1,,0,0,0,,or the notion that freedom\Nof speech was a sacred right
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.04,0:23:07.97,English1,,0,0,0,,of every individual.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.01,0:23:10.84,English1,,0,0,0,,Expressing an idea that didn't\Nconform to traditional belief
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.88,0:23:13.48,English1,,0,0,0,,could land you in deep trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.48,0:23:18.15,English1,,0,0,0,,Recklessly, Bruno returned to Italy.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.18,0:23:19.82,English1,,0,0,0,,Maybe he was homesick.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.85,0:23:23.09,English1,,0,0,0,,But still, he must have known\Nthat his homeland
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.12,0:23:25.19,English1,,0,0,0,,was one of the most dangerous\Nplaces in Europe
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.22,0:23:26.96,English1,,0,0,0,,he could possibly go.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.99,0:23:30.03,English1,,0,0,0,,The Roman Catholic Church\Nmaintained a system of courts
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.06,0:23:31.86,English1,,0,0,0,,known as the Inquisition,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.90,0:23:35.43,English1,,0,0,0,,and its sole purpose was to investigate and torment
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.47,0:23:39.34,English1,,0,0,0,,anyone who dared voice views that differed from theirs.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.38,0:23:46.31,English1,,0,0,0,,It wasn't long before Bruno fell into the clutches
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.35,0:23:48.21,English1,,0,0,0,,of the thought police.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.25,0:23:56.89,English1,,0,0,0,,This wanderer, who worshiped\N{\i1}an infinite universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.92,0:24:00.06,English1,,0,0,0,,languished in confinement for eight years.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.09,0:24:01.89,English1,,0,0,0,,Through relentless interrogations,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.93,0:24:04.63,English1,,0,0,0,,he stubbornly refused to renounce his views.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.66,0:24:06.20,English1,,0,0,0,,Why was the Church willing
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.23,0:24:09.90,English1,,0,0,0,,to go to such lengths to torment Bruno?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.94,0:24:11.97,English1,,0,0,0,,What were they afraid of?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.00,0:24:15.21,English1,,0,0,0,,If Bruno was right, then the sacred books
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.24,0:24:17.38,English1,,0,0,0,,and the authority of the Church
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.41,0:24:20.75,English1,,0,0,0,,would be open to question.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.78,0:24:22.48,English1,,0,0,0,,Finally, the cardinals of the Inquisition
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.52,0:24:24.42,English1,,0,0,0,,rendered their verdict.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.45,0:24:26.02,English1,,0,0,0,,You are found guilty
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.05,0:24:28.89,English1,,0,0,0,,of questioning the Holy Trinity
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.92,0:24:31.59,English1,,0,0,0,,and the divinity of Jesus Christ.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.62,0:24:34.89,English1,,0,0,0,,Of believing that God's wrath is not eternal,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.93,0:24:36.40,English1,,0,0,0,,that everyone will be saved.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.43,0:24:41.23,English1,,0,0,0,,Of asserting the existence of other worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.37,0:24:45.27,English1,,0,0,0,,All of the books you have written
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.30,0:24:48.77,English1,,0,0,0,,will be gathered up and burned in St. Peter's Square.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.81,0:24:52.38,English1,,0,0,0,,Reverend Father, these eight years of confinement
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.41,0:24:53.95,English1,,0,0,0,,have given me much time to reflect.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.98,0:24:54.95,English1,,0,0,0,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.98,0:24:56.35,English1,,0,0,0,,you will recant?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.38,0:24:58.35,English1,,0,0,0,,My love and reverence for the Creator
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.38,0:25:02.02,English1,,0,0,0,,inspires in me the vision of an infinite Creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.06,0:25:05.62,English1,,0,0,0,,You shall be turned over to the Governor of Rome
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.66,0:25:09.03,English1,,0,0,0,,to administer the appropriate punishment
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.06,0:25:11.13,English1,,0,0,0,,for those who will not repent.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.23,0:25:17.14,English1,,0,0,0,,It may be that you are more afraid
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.17,0:25:20.51,English1,,0,0,0,,to deliver this judgment than I am to hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.64,0:26:30.88,English1,,0,0,0,,Ten years after Bruno's martyrdom,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.91,0:26:33.35,English1,,0,0,0,,Galileo first looked through a telescope,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.38,0:26:36.01,English1,,0,0,0,,realizing that Bruno had been right all along.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.05,0:26:38.78,English1,,0,0,0,,The Milky Way was made of countless stars
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.82,0:26:40.52,English1,,0,0,0,,invisible to the naked eye,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.55,0:26:44.49,English1,,0,0,0,,and some of those lights in the\Nsky were actually other worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.52,0:26:46.79,English1,,0,0,0,,Bruno was no scientist.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.83,0:26:49.29,English1,,0,0,0,,His vision of the cosmos was a lucky guess,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.33,0:26:51.80,English1,,0,0,0,,because he had no evidence to support it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.83,0:26:55.07,English1,,0,0,0,,Like most guesses, it could\Nwell have turned out wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.10,0:26:57.67,English1,,0,0,0,,But once the idea was in the air,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.70,0:26:59.74,English1,,0,0,0,,it gave others a target to aim at.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.77,0:27:01.37,English1,,0,0,0,,If only to disprove it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.41,0:27:07.08,English1,,0,0,0,,Bruno glimpsed the vastness of space.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.11,0:27:11.88,English1,,0,0,0,,But he had no inkling of the\N{\i1}staggering immensity of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.46,0:27:18.52,English1,,0,0,0,,How can we humans, who rarely\Nlive more than a century,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.56,0:27:21.33,English1,,0,0,0,,hope to grasp the vast expanse of time
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.36,0:27:23.56,English1,,0,0,0,,that is the history of the cosmos?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.60,0:27:28.37,English1,,0,0,0,,The universe is 13.8 thousand million years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.40,0:27:30.77,English1,,0,0,0,,In order to imagine all of cosmic time,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.80,0:27:34.44,English1,,0,0,0,,let's compress it into a single calendar year.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.57,0:27:51.56,English1,,0,0,0,,The cosmic calendar begins on January 1st\Nwith the birth of our universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.59,0:27:54.24,English1,,0,0,0,,It contains everything that's\Nhappened since then,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.28,0:27:55.33,English1,,0,0,0,,up to now,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.37,0:27:59.89,English1,,0,0,0,,which on this calendar\Nis midnight December 31st.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.92,0:28:03.86,English1,,0,0,0,,On this scale, every month\Nrepresents about a billion years.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.89,0:28:08.42,English1,,0,0,0,,Every day represents nearly 40 million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.45,0:28:10.31,English1,,0,0,0,,Let's go back as far as we can,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.34,0:28:13.49,English1,,0,0,0,,to the very first moment of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.43,0:28:18.35,English1,,0,0,0,,January 1st, the Big Bang.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.16,0:28:32.29,English1,,0,0,0,,It's as far back as we can see in time...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.96,0:28:34.61,English1,,0,0,0,,for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.79,0:28:40.52,English1,,0,0,0,,Our entire universe emerged from\Na point smaller than a single atom.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.62,0:28:43.58,English1,,0,0,0,,Space itself exploded in a cosmic fire,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.62,0:28:45.95,English1,,0,0,0,,launching the expansion of the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.99,0:28:48.36,English1,,0,0,0,,and giving birth to all the energy
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.39,0:28:50.32,English1,,0,0,0,,and all the matter we know today.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.36,0:28:52.66,English1,,0,0,0,,I know that sounds crazy,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.69,0:28:54.63,English1,,0,0,0,,but there's strong observational evidence
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.66,0:28:56.26,English1,,0,0,0,,to support the Big Bang theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.30,0:28:58.77,English1,,0,0,0,,And it includes the amount\Nof helium in the cosmos
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.80,0:29:02.44,English1,,0,0,0,,and the glow of radio waves\Nleft over from the explosion.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.47,0:29:04.94,English1,,0,0,0,,As it expanded, the universe cooled,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.97,0:29:09.84,English1,,0,0,0,,and there was darkness\Nfor about 200 million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.88,0:29:12.81,English1,,0,0,0,,Gravity was pulling together\Nclumps of gas and heating them
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.85,0:29:15.82,English1,,0,0,0,,until the first stars burst into light
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.85,0:29:18.05,English1,,0,0,0,,on January 10th.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.99,0:29:26.79,English1,,0,0,0,,On January 13th, these stars coalesced
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.83,0:29:31.70,English1,,0,0,0,,into the first small galaxies.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.73,0:29:34.54,English1,,0,0,0,,These galaxies merged to form still larger ones,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.57,0:29:37.91,English1,,0,0,0,,including our own Milky Way,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.94,0:29:42.38,English1,,0,0,0,,which formed about 11 billion years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.41,0:29:45.25,English1,,0,0,0,,on March 15th of the cosmic year.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.12,0:29:49.58,English1,,0,0,0,,Hundreds of billions of suns.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.62,0:29:51.42,English1,,0,0,0,,Which one is ours?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.45,0:29:53.65,English1,,0,0,0,,It's not yet born.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.69,0:29:58.16,English1,,0,0,0,,It will rise from the ashes of other stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.19,0:30:01.40,English1,,0,0,0,,See those lights flashing like paparazzi?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.43,0:30:03.86,English1,,0,0,0,,Each one is a supernova,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.90,0:30:07.03,English1,,0,0,0,,the blazing death of a giant star.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.07,0:30:10.44,English1,,0,0,0,,Stars die and are born\N{\i1}in places like this one...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.47,0:30:12.34,English1,,0,0,0,,a stellar nursery.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.37,0:30:14.04,English1,,0,0,0,,They condense like raindrops
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.08,0:30:16.71,English1,,0,0,0,,from giant clouds of gas and dust.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.75,0:30:19.71,English1,,0,0,0,,They get so hot that the nuclei of the atoms
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.75,0:30:22.25,English1,,0,0,0,,fuse together deep within them
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.28,0:30:25.45,English1,,0,0,0,,to make the oxygen we breathe,\N{\i1}the carbon in our muscles,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.49,0:30:28.92,English1,,0,0,0,,the calcium in our bones,\N{\i1}the iron in our blood,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.96,0:30:30.72,English1,,0,0,0,,all of it was cooked
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.76,0:30:34.23,English1,,0,0,0,,in the fiery hearts of long-vanished stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.26,0:30:37.97,English1,,0,0,0,,You, me, everyone...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.00,0:30:42.44,English1,,0,0,0,,we are made of star stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.24,0:30:46.54,English1,,0,0,0,,This star stuff is recycled and enriched,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.57,0:30:48.11,English1,,0,0,0,,again and again,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.14,0:30:50.81,English1,,0,0,0,,through succeeding generations of stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.08,0:30:57.45,English1,,0,0,0,,How much longer until the birth of our Sun?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.49,0:30:59.25,English1,,0,0,0,,A long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.29,0:31:00.55,English1,,0,0,0,,It won't begin to shine
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.59,0:31:03.42,English1,,0,0,0,,for another six billion years.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.13,0:31:08.10,English1,,0,0,0,,Our Sun's birthday is August 31st
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.13,0:31:09.93,English1,,0,0,0,,on the Cosmic Calendar...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.47,0:31:14.74,English1,,0,0,0,,...four and a half billion years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.77,0:31:17.24,English1,,0,0,0,,As with the other worlds of our solar system,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.27,0:31:20.34,English1,,0,0,0,,Earth was formed from a disk of gas and dust
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.38,0:31:22.51,English1,,0,0,0,,orbiting the newborn Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.54,0:31:25.98,English1,,0,0,0,,Repeated collisions produced\Na growing ball of debris.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.39,0:31:33.79,English1,,0,0,0,,See that asteroid?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.82,0:31:35.12,English1,,0,0,0,,No, not that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.16,0:31:36.82,English1,,0,0,0,,The one over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.86,0:31:40.59,English1,,0,0,0,,We exist because the gravity\N{\i1}of that one next to it
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.63,0:31:43.76,English1,,0,0,0,,just nudged it an inch to the left.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.80,0:31:45.80,English1,,0,0,0,,What difference could an inch make
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.83,0:31:47.87,English1,,0,0,0,,on the scale the solar system?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.90,0:31:50.80,English1,,0,0,0,,Just wait, you'll see.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.37,0:31:54.17,English1,,0,0,0,,The Earth took one hell of a beating
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.21,0:31:56.04,English1,,0,0,0,,in its first billion years.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.48,0:32:02.35,English1,,0,0,0,,Fragments of orbiting debris collided and coalesced,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.38,0:32:04.99,English1,,0,0,0,,until they snowballed to form our Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.16,0:32:10.69,English1,,0,0,0,,The Moon is a souvenir of that violent epoch.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.73,0:32:13.73,English1,,0,0,0,,If you stood on the surface\N{\i1}of that long ago Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.76,0:32:16.46,English1,,0,0,0,,the Moon would have looked\N{\i1}a hundred times brighter.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.50,0:32:18.67,English1,,0,0,0,,It was ten times closer back then,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.70,0:32:23.40,English1,,0,0,0,,locked in a much more intimate\N{\i1}gravitational embrace.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.44,0:32:26.37,English1,,0,0,0,,As the Earth cooled, seas began to form.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.41,0:32:29.48,English1,,0,0,0,,The tides were a thousand times higher then.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.51,0:32:32.71,English1,,0,0,0,,Over the eons,\N{\i1}tidal friction within Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.75,0:32:34.85,English1,,0,0,0,,pushed the Moon away.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.72,0:32:43.42,English1,,0,0,0,,Life began somewhere around here,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.46,0:32:45.53,English1,,0,0,0,,September 21st,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.56,0:32:48.60,English1,,0,0,0,,three and a half billion\Nyears ago on our little world.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.63,0:32:50.40,English1,,0,0,0,,We still don't know how life got started.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.43,0:32:52.07,English1,,0,0,0,,For all we know,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.10,0:32:54.10,English1,,0,0,0,,it may have come from\Nanother part of the Milky Way.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.14,0:32:55.94,English1,,0,0,0,,The origin of life
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.97,0:32:59.21,English1,,0,0,0,,is one of the greatest\Nunsolved mysteries of science.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.81,0:33:04.85,English1,,0,0,0,,That's life cooking,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.88,0:33:07.41,English1,,0,0,0,,evolving all the biochemical recipes
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.45,0:33:11.12,English1,,0,0,0,,for its incredibly complex activities.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.15,0:33:16.69,English1,,0,0,0,,By November 9th,\N{\i1}life was breathing, moving,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.73,0:33:20.59,English1,,0,0,0,,eating, responding to its environment.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.63,0:33:23.53,English1,,0,0,0,,We owe a lot to those pioneering microbes.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.57,0:33:25.60,English1,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah... one other thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.63,0:33:28.97,English1,,0,0,0,,They also invented sex.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.41,0:33:34.58,English1,,0,0,0,,December 17th was quite a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.61,0:33:37.04,English1,,0,0,0,,Life in the sea really took off,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.08,0:33:39.21,English1,,0,0,0,,it was exploding with a diversity
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.25,0:33:41.22,English1,,0,0,0,,of larger plants and animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.25,0:33:46.35,English1,,0,0,0,,Tiktaalik was one of the first\Nanimals to venture onto land.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.26,0:33:51.63,English1,,0,0,0,,It must have felt like visiting another planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.13,0:33:55.50,English1,,0,0,0,,Forests, dinosaurs,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.53,0:33:57.83,English1,,0,0,0,,birds, insects,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.87,0:34:01.24,English1,,0,0,0,,they all evolved in the final week of December.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.27,0:34:03.10,English1,,0,0,0,,The first flower...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.14,0:34:07.44,English1,,0,0,0,,bloomed on December 28th.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.85,0:34:13.58,English1,,0,0,0,,As these ancient forests grew and died
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.62,0:34:15.58,English1,,0,0,0,,and sank beneath the surface,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.62,0:34:18.45,English1,,0,0,0,,their remains transformed into coal.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.49,0:34:21.09,English1,,0,0,0,,300 million years later,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.12,0:34:24.43,English1,,0,0,0,,we humans are burning most of that coal to power
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.46,0:34:27.53,English1,,0,0,0,,and imperil our civilization.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.50,0:34:33.87,English1,,0,0,0,,Remember that asteroid back in the formation
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.90,0:34:35.54,English1,,0,0,0,,of the solar system...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.57,0:34:37.71,English1,,0,0,0,,the one that got nudged a little to the left?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.74,0:34:40.04,English1,,0,0,0,,Well, here it comes.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.08,0:34:42.51,English1,,0,0,0,,It's 6:24 AM
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.54,0:34:46.85,English1,,0,0,0,,on December 30th on the Cosmic Calendar.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.86,0:34:55.79,English1,,0,0,0,,For more than a hundred million years,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.82,0:34:58.03,English1,,0,0,0,,the dinosaurs were lords of the Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.06,0:35:00.80,English1,,0,0,0,,while our ancestors, small mammals,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.83,0:35:02.96,English1,,0,0,0,,scurried fearfully underfoot.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.00,0:35:05.37,English1,,0,0,0,,The asteroid changed all that.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.40,0:35:07.20,English1,,0,0,0,,Suppose it hadn't been nudged at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.24,0:35:09.04,English1,,0,0,0,,It would have missed the Earth entirely,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.07,0:35:11.34,English1,,0,0,0,,and for all we know, the\Ndinosaurs might still be here
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.37,0:35:12.97,English1,,0,0,0,,but we wouldn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.01,0:35:15.98,English1,,0,0,0,,This is a good example of the extreme contingency,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.01,0:35:18.75,English1,,0,0,0,,the chance nature, of existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.42,0:35:23.68,English1,,0,0,0,,The universe is already more than 13 and a half
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.72,0:35:25.09,English1,,0,0,0,,billion years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.12,0:35:26.92,English1,,0,0,0,,Still no sign of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.96,0:35:31.09,English1,,0,0,0,,In the vast ocean of time that this calendar represents,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.13,0:35:34.20,English1,,0,0,0,,we humans only evolved within the last hour
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.23,0:35:39.23,English1,,0,0,0,,of the last day of the cosmic year.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.61,0:35:48.34,English1,,0,0,0,,11:59 and 46 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.38,0:35:52.58,English1,,0,0,0,,All of recorded history occupies only the last 14 seconds,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.61,0:35:55.35,English1,,0,0,0,,and every person you've ever heard of
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.38,0:35:57.39,English1,,0,0,0,,lived somewhere in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.25,0:36:03.19,English1,,0,0,0,,All those kings and battles,\Nmigrations and inventions,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.23,0:36:07.70,English1,,0,0,0,,wars and loves, everything in the history books
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.73,0:36:09.76,English1,,0,0,0,,happened here, in the last seconds
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.80,0:36:11.87,English1,,0,0,0,,of the Cosmic Calendar.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.90,0:36:14.07,English1,,0,0,0,,But if we want to explore
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.10,0:36:16.64,English1,,0,0,0,,such a brief moment of cosmic time...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.27,0:36:21.34,English1,,0,0,0,,...we'll have to change scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.21,0:36:40.57,English1,,0,0,0,,We are newcomers to the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.61,0:36:45.01,English1,,0,0,0,,Our own story only begins on the\Nlast night of the cosmic year.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.05,0:36:48.42,English1,,0,0,0,,It's 9:45 on New Year's Eve.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.45,0:36:50.85,English1,,0,0,0,,Three and a half million years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.89,0:36:54.79,English1,,0,0,0,,our ancestors, yours and mine, left these traces.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.16,0:36:59.79,English1,,0,0,0,,We stood up, and parted ways from them.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.83,0:37:01.73,English1,,0,0,0,,Once we were standing on two feet,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.76,0:37:04.90,English1,,0,0,0,,our eyes were no longer fixated on the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.93,0:37:08.57,English1,,0,0,0,,Now we were free to look up in wonder.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.17,0:37:13.64,English1,,0,0,0,,For the longest part of human existence,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.68,0:37:17.41,English1,,0,0,0,,say the last 40,000 generations,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.45,0:37:19.25,English1,,0,0,0,,we were wanderers,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.28,0:37:22.45,English1,,0,0,0,,living in small bands of hunters and gatherers,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.48,0:37:25.12,English1,,0,0,0,,making tools, controlling fire,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.15,0:37:27.12,English1,,0,0,0,,naming things,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.16,0:37:31.49,English1,,0,0,0,,all within the last hour of the Cosmic Calendar.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.63,0:37:43.10,English1,,0,0,0,,To find out what happens next, we'll have to change scale
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.14,0:37:46.31,English1,,0,0,0,,to see the last minute of the last night
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.34,0:37:49.34,English1,,0,0,0,,of the cosmic year.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.38,0:37:51.35,English1,,0,0,0,,11:59
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.38,0:37:54.01,English1,,0,0,0,,We're so very young on the time scale of the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.05,0:37:56.65,English1,,0,0,0,,that we didn't start painting our first pictures
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.68,0:38:00.25,English1,,0,0,0,,until the last 60 seconds of the cosmic year,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.29,0:38:03.79,English1,,0,0,0,,a mere 30,000 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.03,0:38:14.60,English1,,0,0,0,,This is when we invented astronomy.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.64,0:38:17.80,English1,,0,0,0,,In fact, we're all descended from astronomers.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.84,0:38:21.21,English1,,0,0,0,,Our survival depended on\N{\i1}knowing how to read the stars
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.24,0:38:23.54,English1,,0,0,0,,in order to predict the coming of the winter
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.58,0:38:26.18,English1,,0,0,0,,and the migration of the wild herds.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.21,0:38:29.18,English1,,0,0,0,,And then, around 10,000 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.22,0:38:32.19,English1,,0,0,0,,there began a revolution in the way we lived.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.22,0:38:35.46,English1,,0,0,0,,Our ancestors learned\N{\i1}how to shape their environment,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.49,0:38:37.86,English1,,0,0,0,,taming wild plants and animals,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.89,0:38:40.86,English1,,0,0,0,,cultivating land and settling down.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.90,0:38:43.46,English1,,0,0,0,,This changed everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.50,0:38:45.47,English1,,0,0,0,,For the first time in our history,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.50,0:38:48.87,English1,,0,0,0,,we had more stuff than we could carry.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.90,0:38:51.31,English1,,0,0,0,,We needed a way to keep track of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.34,0:38:53.51,English1,,0,0,0,,At 14 seconds to midnight,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.54,0:38:57.01,English1,,0,0,0,,or about 6,000 years ago, we invented writing.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.05,0:38:59.51,English1,,0,0,0,,And it wasn't long before we started recording
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.55,0:39:01.25,English1,,0,0,0,,more than bushels of grain.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.28,0:39:03.25,English1,,0,0,0,,Writing allowed us to save our thoughts
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.28,0:39:06.52,English1,,0,0,0,,and send them much further in space and time.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.55,0:39:08.92,English1,,0,0,0,,Tiny markings on a clay tablet
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.96,0:39:12.19,English1,,0,0,0,,became a means for us to vanquish mortality.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.23,0:39:15.33,English1,,0,0,0,,It shook the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.36,0:39:18.43,English1,,0,0,0,,Moses was born seven seconds ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.47,0:39:21.37,English1,,0,0,0,,Buddha, six seconds ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.40,0:39:24.27,English1,,0,0,0,,Jesus, five seconds ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.31,0:39:27.71,English1,,0,0,0,,Mohammed, three seconds ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.74,0:39:31.11,English1,,0,0,0,,It was not even two seconds ago that, for better or worse,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.15,0:39:34.45,English1,,0,0,0,,the two halves of the Earth discovered each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.48,0:39:36.72,English1,,0,0,0,,And it was only in the very last second
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.75,0:39:39.72,English1,,0,0,0,,of the Cosmic Calendar that we began to use science
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.75,0:39:42.89,English1,,0,0,0,,to reveal nature's secrets and her laws.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.92,0:39:45.63,English1,,0,0,0,,The scientific method is so powerful
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.66,0:39:47.63,English1,,0,0,0,,that in a mere four centuries,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.66,0:39:50.96,English1,,0,0,0,,it has taken us from Galileo's first look through a telescope
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.00,0:39:54.47,English1,,0,0,0,,at another world to leaving our footprints on the Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.50,0:39:58.97,English1,,0,0,0,,It allowed us to look out across space and time
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.01,0:40:04.75,English1,,0,0,0,,to discover where and when we are in the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.78,0:40:09.32,English1,,0,0,0,,We are a way for the cosmos to know itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.35,0:40:11.65,English1,,0,0,0,,Carl Sagan guided the maiden voyage of Cosmos
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.69,0:40:13.42,English1,,0,0,0,,a generation ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.45,0:40:15.62,English1,,0,0,0,,He was the most successful\Nscience communicator
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.66,0:40:17.12,English1,,0,0,0,,of the 20th century,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.16,0:40:19.89,English1,,0,0,0,,but he was first and foremost a scientist.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.93,0:40:23.43,English1,,0,0,0,,Carl contributed enormously
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.47,0:40:25.63,English1,,0,0,0,,to our knowledge of the planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.67,0:40:28.64,English1,,0,0,0,,He correctly predicted the existence of methane lakes
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.67,0:40:30.64,English1,,0,0,0,,on Saturn's giant moon Titan.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.67,0:40:33.94,English1,,0,0,0,,He showed that the atmosphere of the early Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.98,0:40:36.91,English1,,0,0,0,,must have contained powerful greenhouse gases.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.95,0:40:40.91,English1,,0,0,0,,He was the first to understand\N{\i1}that seasonal changes on Mars
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.95,0:40:43.42,English1,,0,0,0,,were due to windblown dust.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.45,0:40:44.99,English1,,0,0,0,,Carl was a pioneer
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.02,0:40:46.42,English1,,0,0,0,,in the search for extraterrestrial life
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.45,0:40:49.32,English1,,0,0,0,,and intelligence.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.36,0:40:52.63,English1,,0,0,0,,He played a leading role in\N{\i1}every major spacecraft mission
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.66,0:40:55.13,English1,,0,0,0,,to explore the solar system during the first 40 years
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.16,0:40:57.53,English1,,0,0,0,,of the Space Age.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.30,0:41:02.17,English1,,0,0,0,,But that's not all he did.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.41,0:41:08.51,English1,,0,0,0,,This is Carl Sagan's own calendar from 1975.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.48,0:41:13.48,English1,,0,0,0,,Who was I back then?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.52,0:41:16.32,English1,,0,0,0,,I was just a 17-year-old kid from the Bronx
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.35,0:41:18.72,English1,,0,0,0,,with dreams of becoming a scientist,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.75,0:41:22.06,English1,,0,0,0,,and somehow the world's most\Nfamous astronomer found time
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.09,0:41:24.89,English1,,0,0,0,,to invite me to Ithaca, in upstate New York,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.93,0:41:26.69,English1,,0,0,0,,and spend a Saturday with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.73,0:41:30.13,English1,,0,0,0,,I remember that snowy day like it was yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.17,0:41:31.97,English1,,0,0,0,,He met me at the bus stop
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.00,0:41:34.87,English1,,0,0,0,,and showed me his laboratory at Cornell University.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.90,0:41:39.34,English1,,0,0,0,,Carl reached behind his desk\Nand inscribed this book for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.08,0:41:45.75,English1,,0,0,0,,"For Neil, a future astronomer.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.78,0:41:47.58,English1,,0,0,0,,Carl."
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.62,0:41:51.02,English1,,0,0,0,,At the end of the day, he drove\Nme back to the bus station.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.05,0:41:53.02,English1,,0,0,0,,The snow was falling harder.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.05,0:41:55.02,English1,,0,0,0,,He wrote his phone number...\Nhis home phone number...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.06,0:41:58.53,English1,,0,0,0,,on a scrap of paper and he said,\N"If the bus can't get through,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.56,0:42:02.36,English1,,0,0,0,,call me and spend the night at my home with my family."
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.40,0:42:05.20,English1,,0,0,0,,I already knew I wanted to become a scientist,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.23,0:42:07.60,English1,,0,0,0,,but that afternoon, I learned from Carl
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.64,0:42:09.87,English1,,0,0,0,,the kind of person I wanted to become.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.90,0:42:13.54,English1,,0,0,0,,He reached out to me and to countless others,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.58,0:42:18.05,English1,,0,0,0,,inspiring so many of us to study, teach and do science.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.08,0:42:20.45,English1,,0,0,0,,Science is a cooperative enterprise,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.48,0:42:22.85,English1,,0,0,0,,spanning the generations.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.88,0:42:27.19,English1,,0,0,0,,It's the passing of a torch from\Nteacher to student to teacher,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.22,0:42:30.69,English1,,0,0,0,,a community of minds\Nreaching back to antiquity
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.73,0:42:32.69,English1,,0,0,0,,and forward to the stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.73,0:42:35.53,English1,,0,0,0,,Now, come with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.56,0:42:38.97,English1,,0,0,0,,Our journey is just beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.05,0:43:14.44,English1,,0,0,0,,Sync and corrections by n17t01\Nwww.addic7ed.com
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.83,0:00:03.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}宇宙就是这样
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.58,0:00:04.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}过去是这样
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.28,0:00:06.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}以后还是这样
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.73,0:00:09.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}跟我来
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.53,0:00:12.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}30多年前
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.54,0:00:14.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}天文学家卡尔·萨根站在这里
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.94,0:00:16.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,带领全世界数亿人
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.94,0:00:18.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,进行了一场历险
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.94,0:00:22.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,用科学去探索宇宙的奥秘
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.78,0:00:25.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,,是时候再次探险了
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.78,0:00:28.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这场即将开始的旅行会向我们展示
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.79,0:00:31.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,从最微小的到无穷大的
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.89,0:00:34.86,Chinese,,0,0,0,,从时间的开始到遥远的未来
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.89,0:00:39.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们会探索不同的世界和星系
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.23,0:00:42.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在时间和空间的组合中畅游
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.27,0:00:45.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}接触生活在火中和冰中的生物
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.64,0:00:49.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}探索永恒不灭的星系
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.41,0:00:51.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}了解和恒星一样大的原子
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.01,0:00:56.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}还有比原子还小的宇宙
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.11,0:00:59.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这也是关于人类的故事
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.28,0:01:03.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这也是先人们对星空研究的史诗长篇
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.45,0:01:08.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这也是先人们对星空研究的史诗长篇
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.16,0:01:11.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}众多英雄共同谱写的史诗
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.64,0:01:24.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们需要想象力来完成这次历险
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.14,0:01:26.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但仅靠想象力是不够的
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.48,0:01:29.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为大自然的真实样子是超乎想象的神奇
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.68,0:01:32.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为大自然的真实样子是超乎想象的神奇
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.05,0:01:39.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,几代研究人员的努力使这次的历险成为可能
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.72,0:01:43.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们严格地坚持一套简单的规则
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.23,0:01:47.03,Chinese,,0,0,0,,以试验和观察结果检验观点
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.06,0:01:49.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,以通过检验的观点为基础
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.00,0:01:52.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,摒弃未通过检验的
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.24,0:01:54.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,用证据说话
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.87,0:01:57.51,Chinese,,0,0,0,,并对一切存疑
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.54,0:02:00.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,接受这些规则
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.04,0:02:03.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,,宇宙就是你的
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.01,0:02:07.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,跟我来吧
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.30,0:04:04.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在这艘想象之船中
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.30,0:04:06.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不受空间和时间的限制
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.94,0:04:09.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们可以去任何地方
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.01,0:04:12.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果你想知道我们身处太空何处
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.28,0:04:15.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,只要看向窗外
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.38,0:04:23.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,以时间来说，过去就在我们脚下
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.32,0:04:29.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这就是地球2.5亿年前的样子
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.13,0:04:35.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,抬头，就可以看到未来的样子
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.73,0:04:41.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这就是2.5亿年后可能的样子
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.37,0:04:43.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果我们要尝试
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.84,0:04:46.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在极度广阔的宇宙中联系
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.71,0:04:49.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们需要知道自己的宇宙地址
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.65,0:04:53.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这就是我们地址的第一行
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.35,0:04:57.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,地球
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.54,0:05:18.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们现在离开地球，这个我们仅有的家园
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.94,0:05:23.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}向极度宽广的宇宙进发
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.38,0:05:31.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们最近的邻居，月球，没有大气层
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.29,0:05:34.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}没有海洋，没有生命
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.72,0:05:38.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}只有天体撞击的伤痕
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.11,0:05:54.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}太阳为风和浪提供能量
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.11,0:05:57.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}为地球表面一切的生物提供能量
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.95,0:06:00.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}整个太阳系都被太阳的引力场所包围
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.55,0:06:05.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}从水星开始
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.64,0:06:27.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}到云层覆盖的金星，失控温室效应
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.58,0:06:31.18,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}把它变成一处炼狱
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.12,0:06:38.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}火星
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.96,0:06:43.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}表面积和地球相近
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.14,0:06:59.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}一条岩石似的小行星带
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.48,0:07:01.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在火星和木星的轨道间围绕太阳运行
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.46,0:07:17.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}木星被四个大卫星和几十个小卫星环绕
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.79,0:07:21.26,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}木星好像拥有自己的太阳系一般
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.30,0:07:25.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}它的质量超过所有其他行星的总和
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.35,0:07:39.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}木星的大红斑
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.35,0:07:42.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}它是一个比地球大3倍的古老风暴
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.52,0:07:46.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}已经存在了几百年之久
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.51,0:08:10.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}土星宛如太阳系中皇冠上的明珠
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.41,0:08:13.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}被无数运行轨道和缓慢翻滚的雪球所环绕
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.68,0:08:16.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}被无数运行轨道和缓慢翻滚的雪球所环绕
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.09,0:08:20.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}每个雪球都是一个小月亮
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.72,0:08:53.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}天王星
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.92,0:08:55.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}还有海王星
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.93,0:09:00.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这颗古人未知的最偏远的行星
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.26,0:09:05.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}直到望远镜发明后才被发现
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.44,0:09:08.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在这最偏远的行星之外
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.84,0:09:13.51,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}还有成千上万的冰冻世界
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.03,0:09:33.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}冥王星就是其中一个
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.34,0:09:48.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在我们所有的航天器中
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.78,0:09:52.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这是离家最远的一个
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.12,0:09:55.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}旅行者1号
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.35,0:09:59.99,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}她承载着我们发向未来的信息
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.02,0:10:02.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}关于我们是谁
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.79,0:10:04.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们的体会
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.96,0:10:06.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}以及我们创作的音乐
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.18,0:10:20.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}浩瀚宇宙海洋中
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.04,0:10:21.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}更深层的水流里
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.91,0:10:25.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}存在着数不尽的世界
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.64,0:10:41.51,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}从这里看，太阳好像和其他星星并无两样
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.54,0:10:43.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但它的引力场依然影响着
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.98,0:10:46.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,数万亿的冰冻彗星
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.38,0:10:49.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}还有太阳系中那些形成于大约50亿年前的
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.15,0:10:51.95,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}其他所有组成部分
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.98,0:10:54.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们称之为 奥尔特云
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.62,0:10:57.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}以前从没有人见过，也不可能见过
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.36,0:10:59.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}因为这些天体
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.63,0:11:01.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}与它最近的邻居之间的距离
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.86,0:11:05.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}和地球与土星的距离差不多 (12-16亿公里）
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.50,0:11:09.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个包含太阳系的巨大彗星云团
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.33,0:11:13.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就是我们宇宙地址的第二行
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.14,0:11:16.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,,地球\N太阳系
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.04,0:11:21.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们有能力探测其他星系的行星
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.71,0:11:23.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}也就是最近几十年的事情
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.72,0:11:27.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}但是我们已经知道行星的数量是很多的
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.49,0:11:30.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}比恒星的数量要多得多
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.16,0:11:33.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}几乎所有的行星都和地球很不一样
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.59,0:11:36.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}不适合生物生存
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.09,0:11:38.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}但是我们对于生物又有多少了解呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.50,0:11:41.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}目前我们只接触过一种
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.57,0:11:43.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}地球生物
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.54,0:11:44.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,看到什么了吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.87,0:11:46.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,只是空荡荡的太空 对吗
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.87,0:11:49.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,人类的眼睛只能看到
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.68,0:11:51.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,宇宙中的一丝光亮
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.68,0:11:55.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是科技让我们可以看到肉眼无法看到的
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.91,0:11:58.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,夜视镜可以让我们看见红外线
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.68,0:12:00.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,夜视镜可以让我们看见红外线
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.72,0:12:03.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,向黑暗中发射一个红外感应器
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.79,0:12:06.39,Chinese,,0,0,0,,流浪行星
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.43,0:12:08.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不绕恒星公转的行星
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.60,0:12:15.03,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们的银河中有数十亿颗游荡在永恒的黑夜中
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.07,0:12:18.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在他们原本的星系诞生时的混乱中
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.64,0:12:22.07,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们像孤儿一样失去了恒星母亲
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.81,0:12:26.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}流浪行星有着熔岩般的内核
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.48,0:12:28.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}但是冰冻的表面
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.48,0:12:30.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在这些极端区域的中间
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.48,0:12:33.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}也许存在着大洋般的液体水
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.06,0:12:41.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}谁又能知道水中生活着什么东西呢
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.43,0:12:49.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这是银河的红外线显示图
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.64,0:12:52.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,每个小点，不仅仅是那些明亮的
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.74,0:12:54.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,都是一颗恒星
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.94,0:12:56.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,多少恒星？
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.94,0:12:58.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,多少行星？
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.94,0:13:01.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,,多少种生命存在的方式？
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.45,0:13:04.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们身处图片中的何处？
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.45,0:13:06.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}看到那条螺旋臂了吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.92,0:13:09.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们就在那里
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.12,0:13:12.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}距离中心3万光年
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.36,0:13:14.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}银河系
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.09,0:13:17.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们宇宙地址的下一行
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.43,0:13:19.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们现在离家十万光年
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.83,0:13:23.07,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}光波，存在的速度最快的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.10,0:13:26.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}要花10万年才能从地球到达我们这里
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.71,0:13:32.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这是仙女座螺旋星系
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.14,0:13:34.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,,银河系的隔壁邻居
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.15,0:13:36.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们将这两大星系
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.15,0:13:38.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,和一些较小的星系称为
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.15,0:13:40.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,本星系群
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.58,0:13:46.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,,地球，太阳系，银河系，本星系群
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.16,0:13:51.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}从这里已经看不到银河系了
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.50,0:13:55.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}它只是室女座超星系团中的几千份之一
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.73,0:13:57.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}以这个比例来说
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.67,0:14:01.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们所看到的，哪怕最小的点
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.31,0:14:03.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,,都是一个星系
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.14,0:14:05.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}每个星系包含几十亿颗恒星
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.71,0:14:07.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}和数不清的行星世界
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.81,0:14:11.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}然而，整个室女座超星系团
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.48,0:14:14.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}只是我们宇宙的一个极小组成部分
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.39,0:14:20.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这是我们已知的最大范围的宇宙
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.39,0:14:23.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}一张由数以千亿的星系组成的大网
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.73,0:14:27.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}也是我们宇宙地址的最后一行
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.20,0:14:29.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}截止目前
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.20,0:14:30.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,,地球，太阳系，银河系，本星系群\N室女座超星系团，可观测宇宙
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.77,0:14:32.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}可观测宇宙
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.27,0:14:34.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,什么意思
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.17,0:14:36.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,即使我们在想象之船中
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.94,0:14:40.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在时空中所能看到的也是有限的
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.58,0:14:42.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这是我们的宇宙水平线
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.02,0:14:46.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一部分的宇宙处于水平线之下
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.12,0:14:48.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,离我们实在太遥远了
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.29,0:14:50.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在仅有的时间里
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.29,0:14:53.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在宇宙138亿年的历史中
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.39,0:14:55.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,光线还来不及传递过来
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.93,0:15:01.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}很多人猜测，所有的这一切
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.37,0:15:05.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}所有的行星，恒星，星系，星团
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.60,0:15:08.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们的可观测宇宙中得一切
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.04,0:15:12.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}只是其他宇宙中得沧海一粟
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.78,0:15:14.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}只是其他宇宙中得沧海一粟
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.42,0:15:18.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}多重宇宙论
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.92,0:15:22.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}宇宙之上的宇宙
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.72,0:15:25.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}没有尽头的世界
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.00,0:15:32.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,,感觉很渺小吗
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.10,0:15:35.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,,相对宇宙来说 我们确实很渺小
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.60,0:15:38.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们或许只是生活在这浩瀚宇宙中
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.94,0:15:41.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,漂浮的尘埃上的小不点
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.34,0:15:43.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但我们并不坐井观天
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.48,0:15:46.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,现在的宇宙论诞生并不久远
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.95,0:15:51.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,仅仅400年前，我们尚未认识
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.25,0:15:53.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,自身世界以外的宇宙
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.25,0:15:55.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那时没有望远镜
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.25,0:15:58.99,Chinese,,0,0,0,,只能看到我们肉眼可见的部分
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.02,0:16:01.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在1599年
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.13,0:16:04.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所有人都认为太阳，行球，星星
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.50,0:16:08.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,只是环绕地球的亮光
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.53,0:16:12.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们是宇宙的中心
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.60,0:16:15.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}由上帝为我们创造的宇宙
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.94,0:16:19.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}当时全世界只有一个人
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.35,0:16:22.18,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}想象着一个无尽的浩瀚宇宙
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.21,0:16:24.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他是怎么度过他的公元1600年除夕？
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.78,0:16:27.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他是怎么度过他的公元1600年除夕？
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.95,0:16:30.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}当然是在监狱里
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.85,0:16:40.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}生命中总有那么一天
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.05,0:16:43.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们发现自己并不是宇宙的中心
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.32,0:16:46.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们以外还有更广大的世界
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.56,0:16:48.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这就是成长
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.56,0:16:50.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,每个人都会经历
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.83,0:16:53.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们的文明也在16世纪经历过这样的成长
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.17,0:16:55.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们的文明也在16世纪经历过这样的成长
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.17,0:16:57.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}想象一下望远镜问世之前
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.07,0:16:59.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们只能靠肉眼观察这个宇宙
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.34,0:17:00.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们只能靠肉眼观察这个宇宙
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.87,0:17:04.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}很显然地球是静止不动的
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.08,0:17:05.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}天空中得一切
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.81,0:17:08.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}太阳 月亮 星星 星球
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.15,0:17:10.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}都围绕着我们运行  然后
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.02,0:17:13.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一位名叫哥白尼的波兰天文学家兼牧师
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.32,0:17:17.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,提出一个地球并非中心的激进假想
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.32,0:17:19.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,,地球只是和其他星星一样的行星
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.83,0:17:21.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,,绕着太阳旋转
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.83,0:17:25.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,很多人 例如宗教改革发起人马丁·路德
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.16,0:17:28.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,认为这是对圣经的可耻侮辱
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.17,0:17:30.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们震怒了
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.44,0:17:34.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是另一个人却认为哥白尼说的不全面
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.91,0:17:38.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他叫焦尔达诺·布鲁诺
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.04,0:17:40.51,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他生性反叛
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.55,0:17:43.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他渴望打破这狭隘宇宙的枷锁
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.75,0:17:46.18,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在那不勒斯做道明会的修道士时
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.22,0:17:48.39,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他就与这个世界格格不入
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.42,0:17:50.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}当时在意大利没有思想的自由
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.76,0:17:52.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}但是布鲁诺渴望了解
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.19,0:17:53.99,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}关于上帝创世的一切
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.03,0:17:56.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他阅读了被教廷禁止的书籍
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.80,0:17:58.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}从此踏上了不归路
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.60,0:18:00.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这些书籍中
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.63,0:18:04.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}有一本作者是1500年前的古罗马人\N（物性论 - 卢克莱修）
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.77,0:18:07.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}向他描述了一个更广阔的宇宙
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.74,0:18:10.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}广阔的犹如他的上帝一般
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.88,0:18:16.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}卢克莱修让他的读者
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.88,0:18:19.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}想象站在宇宙的边缘
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.29,0:18:21.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}向外射出一支箭
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.29,0:18:23.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}如果箭继续前进，那么很明显
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.59,0:18:26.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}宇宙继续向所谓的边缘以外延伸
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.49,0:18:28.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}但是如果箭不继续前进
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.93,0:18:31.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}比方说 撞在一堵墙上
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.63,0:18:34.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}那么墙必然是处在所谓的边缘之外
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.60,0:18:37.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}那么如果你站在这堵墙上向外射箭
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.94,0:18:40.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}也只有这相同的两个结果
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.67,0:18:43.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}要么是飞入无尽的太空
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.08,0:18:45.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}要么是撞在某个障碍物上
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.08,0:18:47.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}然后你又可以站在上面射出另一支箭
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.85,0:18:50.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}无论如何 宇宙是没有界限的
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.45,0:18:53.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}宇宙必然是无尽的
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.75,0:18:56.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}布鲁诺深以为然
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.26,0:18:58.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他崇拜的上帝是全能的
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.62,0:19:02.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}所以他断定 上帝创造的宇宙怎会不是无穷
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.11,0:19:20.95,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}那是他的最后一份稳定工作
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.36,0:19:32.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}后来 当他30岁时
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.79,0:19:36.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他的一个幻觉从此改变他的一生
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.46,0:19:38.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在这个梦中 他认识到了
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.96,0:19:42.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}一个包含在一群行星中的世界
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.03,0:19:45.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}就是他那个时代的宇宙
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.49,0:20:06.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他感到一阵不舒服的害怕
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.06,0:20:07.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}就像脚下的一切
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.59,0:20:10.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}向下坠落
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.23,0:20:12.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}但是他鼓起了勇气
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.74,0:20:23.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我展开自信的翅膀飞向太空
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.58,0:20:27.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}向上高飞至无尽的天空
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.18,0:20:30.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}将一切的压力抛在身后
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.55,0:20:33.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这里没有上 没有下 没有边界
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.95,0:20:35.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}没有中心
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.52,0:20:38.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我看见太阳和其他星星一样
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.96,0:20:42.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}还有其他被行星伴随着的恒星
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.93,0:20:44.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}就像我们的太阳
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.56,0:20:47.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这巨大的启示对他就如同
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.87,0:20:49.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}坠入爱河
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.77,0:20:54.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}布鲁诺变成了一个传教士
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.77,0:20:58.18,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他在欧洲各地宣扬他的宇宙无限论
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.21,0:21:01.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他以为其他上帝的追随者会同样接受
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.81,0:21:04.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这个对于创世的伟大并荣耀的观点
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.88,0:21:07.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我太傻了
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.96,0:21:11.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在他的祖国 他被罗马天主教会开除教籍
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.66,0:21:13.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在他的祖国 他被罗马天主教会开除教籍
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.59,0:21:16.03,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他不仅被瑞士加尔文长老会驱逐出境
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.06,0:21:18.26,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}还被德国的路德教派驱逐出境
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.30,0:21:21.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}布鲁诺接受了一份邀请
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.33,0:21:24.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}去英国牛津大学讲课
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.57,0:21:27.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他认为这是一个机会
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.44,0:21:31.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}可以与他类似的人分享他的观点
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.18,0:21:38.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我来介绍一个对于宇宙的崭新看法
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.28,0:21:41.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,哥白尼是对的
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.35,0:21:43.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们的世界并不是宇宙的中心
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.09,0:21:45.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,地球绕着太阳旋转
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.16,0:21:47.63,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它和其他行星一样
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.66,0:21:49.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但哥白尼只是曙光
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.76,0:21:51.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而我为你们带来日出
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.33,0:21:55.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那些星星和我们炙热的太阳一样
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.43,0:21:57.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,由和地球一样的天体组成
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.67,0:22:00.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们也有自己的含水的地球
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.71,0:22:03.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,上面有着和我们一样高贵的动物植物
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.81,0:22:06.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你是疯了还是太蠢
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.11,0:22:07.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,总所周知只有一个世界
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.88,0:22:10.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那是错误的
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.38,0:22:13.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们全能的上帝创造了一个无边无际的宇宙
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.39,0:22:15.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,其中包含了无数的星球
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.29,0:22:17.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你们那的人没读过亚里斯多德的书吗
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.32,0:22:19.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,或者是圣经吗
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.06,0:22:23.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我请求你摒弃老旧和传统的信仰和权威
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.70,0:22:24.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,让我们重新认识
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.00,0:22:27.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,质疑我们以为已经被证实的一切
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.03,0:22:28.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,异端者
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.17,0:22:29.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,异教徒
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.24,0:22:31.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你们信仰的上帝太小了
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.68,0:22:39.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}明智的人本应该从中吸取了教训
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.08,0:22:42.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,可惜布鲁诺并不是那个人
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.42,0:22:46.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他不停的宣扬自己观点
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.69,0:22:49.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,,尽管这会带来沉痛的代价
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.66,0:22:52.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在他的那个时代，代价是如此的残酷
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.69,0:22:54.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,无情和不寻常的惩罚
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.80,0:23:01.47,Chinese,,0,0,0,,焦尔达诺·布鲁诺生活的那个时代
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.50,0:23:03.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,没有政教分离
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.47,0:23:06.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,没有言论自由神圣不可侵犯
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.04,0:23:07.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,没有言论自由神圣不可侵犯
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.01,0:23:10.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,表达与传统信仰相悖的观点
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.88,0:23:13.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,会带来极大的麻烦
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.48,0:23:18.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,,布鲁诺不顾一切地回到了意大利
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.18,0:23:19.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也许是想家了
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.85,0:23:23.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,可是他必须知道
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.12,0:23:25.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他的祖国对他来说
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.22,0:23:26.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,是最危险的国家
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.99,0:23:30.03,Chinese,,0,0,0,,由罗马天主教会管辖的宗教法庭
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.06,0:23:31.86,Chinese,,0,0,0,,被称为异端裁判所
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.90,0:23:35.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它唯一职责就是审查和折磨
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.47,0:23:39.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,与教会持有不同声音和观点的人
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.38,0:23:46.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,布鲁诺很快就被思想警察抓获
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.35,0:23:48.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,布鲁诺很快就被思想警察抓获
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.25,0:23:56.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这位信奉无限宇宙的流浪者
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.92,0:24:00.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在八年的监狱生涯中饱受煎熬
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.09,0:24:01.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}尽管受尽残酷的审讯
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.93,0:24:04.63,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他依然不愿放弃他的观点
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.66,0:24:06.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}为什么教会要花
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.23,0:24:09.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}如此长的时间来折磨布鲁诺
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.94,0:24:11.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他们在害怕什么
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.00,0:24:15.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}如果布鲁诺是对的 那么这些圣典
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.24,0:24:17.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}还有教会的权威
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.41,0:24:20.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}都会受到质疑
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.78,0:24:22.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}最终 异端裁判所的红衣主教们
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.52,0:24:24.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}做出了他们的判决
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.45,0:24:26.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你有罪
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.05,0:24:28.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你质疑圣父圣子圣灵三位一体
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.92,0:24:31.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你质疑耶稣基督的神威
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.62,0:24:34.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你相信上帝的怒火不会永远
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.93,0:24:36.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所有人都会被宽恕
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.43,0:24:41.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你断言其他世界存在的主张
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.37,0:24:45.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你写的所有书
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.30,0:24:48.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,都会在圣彼得广场前焚毁
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.81,0:24:52.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,尊敬的大人 8年的监禁
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.41,0:24:53.95,Chinese,,0,0,0,,给了我很多时间去反省
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.98,0:24:54.95,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后呢
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.98,0:24:56.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你要放弃你的主张吗
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.38,0:24:58.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我对造物主的爱和崇敬
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.38,0:25:02.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,激发我对全能的上帝的认识
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.06,0:25:05.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你会被移交到罗马总督
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.66,0:25:09.03,Chinese,,0,0,0,,予以执行相应地惩罚
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.06,0:25:11.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果你拒不忏悔的话
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.23,0:25:17.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,可能你宣布这个判决时的恐惧
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.17,0:25:20.51,Chinese,,0,0,0,,比我听到判决的时候更厉害
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.64,0:26:30.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,布鲁诺殉难的10年后
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.91,0:26:33.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,伽利略通过望远镜
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.38,0:26:36.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,发现布鲁诺的学说确实没错
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.05,0:26:38.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,银河系是由肉眼看不到的无数恒星组成
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.82,0:26:40.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,银河系是由肉眼看不到的无数恒星组成
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.55,0:26:44.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,天空中的某些光亮其实是其他的行星
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.52,0:26:46.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,,布鲁诺不是科学家
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.83,0:26:49.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他只是侥幸猜中了
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.33,0:26:51.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为没有证据支持他
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.83,0:26:55.07,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就和其他猜想一样 也有可能不对
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.10,0:26:57.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是这个观点一旦散播出去
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.70,0:26:59.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它就给了其他人一个方向
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.77,0:27:01.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,哪怕只是为了反驳
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.41,0:27:07.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}布鲁诺大致理解了太空的浩瀚无垠
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.11,0:27:11.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}但他对于时间的惊人无际没有丝毫概念
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.46,0:27:18.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,寿命很少超过一个世纪的普通人
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.56,0:27:21.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,怎么可能去理解宇宙的历史
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.36,0:27:23.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就像浩瀚宽阔的时间长河
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.60,0:27:28.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,宇宙诞生于138亿年前
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.40,0:27:30.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,为了更好地想象宇宙的历史
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.80,0:27:34.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们把它压缩成12个月的年历
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.57,0:27:51.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,年历上的1月1号是宇宙诞生的日子
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.59,0:27:54.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,年历上包含了从那以后经历的所有时间
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.28,0:27:55.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一直到现在
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.37,0:27:59.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在这个年历上的12月31号午夜
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.92,0:28:03.86,Chinese,,0,0,0,,按照这个比例 每个月代表10亿年
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.89,0:28:08.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,每天代表将就4千万年
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.45,0:28:10.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,让我们尽可能地回到过去
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.34,0:28:13.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,回到宇宙最开始的时刻
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.43,0:28:18.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,1月1号 宇宙大爆炸
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.16,0:28:32.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这是我们所能看到最早的时间
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.96,0:28:34.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,目前而言
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.79,0:28:40.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,整个宇宙形成于一个比原子还小的点
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.62,0:28:43.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,空间在密度极大温度极高的状态下爆炸
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.62,0:28:45.95,Chinese,,0,0,0,,由此开始了宇宙的扩张
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.99,0:28:48.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,并诞生了所有的能量
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.39,0:28:50.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,已经产生所有我们已知的事物
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.36,0:28:52.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,,听上去很疯狂
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.69,0:28:54.63,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是我们有很强力的观测证据
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.66,0:28:56.26,Chinese,,0,0,0,,来支持宇宙大爆炸理论
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.30,0:28:58.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,证据还有氦元素在宇宙中的比例
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.80,0:29:02.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,以及爆炸残留的发光无线电频谱
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.47,0:29:04.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,,爆炸后宇宙开始冷却
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.97,0:29:09.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,其间有2亿年左右的黑暗
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.88,0:29:12.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,万有引力将气体集聚并且加热
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.85,0:29:15.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,直到第一批恒星发出亮光
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.85,0:29:18.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,相当于1月10号
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.99,0:29:26.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,,1月13号 这些恒星开始结合
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.83,0:29:31.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,形成第一批小星系
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.73,0:29:34.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这些星系融合成更大的星系
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.57,0:29:37.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}包括我们的银河系
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.94,0:29:42.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}产生于110亿年左右
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.41,0:29:45.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}就是宇宙年历上得3月15号
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.12,0:29:49.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,数千亿的恒星中
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.62,0:29:51.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,哪个是我们的太阳
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.45,0:29:53.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,此时尚未诞生
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.69,0:29:58.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它将从其他恒星的灰烬中产生
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.19,0:30:01.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}看到这些犹如闪光灯般的亮光吗
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.43,0:30:03.86,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}每一个都是超新星
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.90,0:30:07.03,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}一颗超大恒星的耀眼爆炸
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.07,0:30:10.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}恒星消亡和诞生的地方
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.47,0:30:12.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们称为星星苗圃 （分子云）
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.37,0:30:14.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他们像雨滴般
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.08,0:30:16.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}从巨大的气态和灰尘云中凝结
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.75,0:30:19.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他们温度高的可以把原子中的原子核
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.75,0:30:22.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}融合在一起
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.28,0:30:25.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}从而产生了我们呼吸的氧气 肌肉中的碳元素
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.49,0:30:28.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}骨头中的钙元素 血中的铁元素
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.96,0:30:30.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}所有的这一切都产生于
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.76,0:30:34.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}从此消亡的恒星炙热的内心
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.26,0:30:37.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你 我 所有人
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.00,0:30:42.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们都是由星辰物质组成
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.24,0:30:46.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}星辰物质被不断循环和浓缩
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.57,0:30:48.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}一遍又一遍
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.14,0:30:50.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}经过几代恒星的诞生消亡
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.08,0:30:57.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}离我们的太阳诞生还有多久
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.49,0:30:59.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}很长时间
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.29,0:31:00.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们太阳的第一次发光
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.59,0:31:03.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,还要再等60亿年
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.13,0:31:08.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}太阳的生日是8月31号
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.13,0:31:09.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在这个宇宙年历上
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.47,0:31:14.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}45亿年前
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.77,0:31:17.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就像太阳系中其他行星
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.27,0:31:20.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,地球在一堆气体和灰尘中产生
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.38,0:31:22.51,Chinese,,0,0,0,,绕着新生的太阳运行
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.54,0:31:25.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,,反复的碰撞产生了一个发光的球状碎片
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.39,0:31:33.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}看到那个小行星了吗
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.82,0:31:35.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}不是那个
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.16,0:31:36.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}那边的那个
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.86,0:31:40.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们的存在归功于它旁边的引力
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.63,0:31:43.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}把它轻轻向左推了一英寸
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.80,0:31:45.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}一英寸有很大的区别吗
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.83,0:31:47.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}按照太阳系的比例来说
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.90,0:31:50.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}稍等 你马上就能看到
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.37,0:31:54.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在最初的10亿年里
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.21,0:31:56.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}地球饱受摧残
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.48,0:32:02.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}任由轨道上的碎片撞击和融合
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.38,0:32:04.99,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}直到他们形成了我们的月亮
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.16,0:32:10.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}月亮是那个暴力纪元的纪念品
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.73,0:32:13.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}如果你站在远古地球的表面
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.76,0:32:16.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}月亮会看上去比现在亮100倍
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.50,0:32:18.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}那时月亮离我们近10倍
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.70,0:32:23.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}被比现在更强大的引力场吸引着
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.44,0:32:26.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}地球冷却下来 海洋形成了
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.41,0:32:29.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}海浪比现在高1000倍
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.51,0:32:32.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}经过极漫长的时间 潮汐的摩擦力
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.75,0:32:34.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}将月球推远
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.72,0:32:43.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,生命差不多在这个时候诞生
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.46,0:32:45.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,9月21号
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.56,0:32:48.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在地球上的35亿年前
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.63,0:32:50.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们依然不知道生命如何起源
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.43,0:32:52.07,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们只是知道
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.10,0:32:54.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,,有可能是来自银河系的其他地方
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.14,0:32:55.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,,生命的起源
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.97,0:32:59.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,是最伟大的未知科学奇迹之一
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.81,0:33:04.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,生命的演变
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.88,0:33:07.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}一切生物化学的进化
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.45,0:33:11.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}充满了无与伦比的复杂活动
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.15,0:33:16.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}到了11月9号 生命开始呼吸 移动
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.73,0:33:20.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}进食和对周遭环境做出反应
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.63,0:33:23.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}多亏了这些有开拓性的微生物
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.57,0:33:25.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}没错 就是这些不起眼的家伙
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.63,0:33:28.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他们还发明了繁殖
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.41,0:33:34.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,12月17号 很特别的一天
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.61,0:33:37.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,海洋中生命的发展开始腾飞
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.08,0:33:39.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,形形色色的大型植物和动物
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.25,0:33:41.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,爆炸式的发展
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.25,0:33:46.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}提塔利克鱼是最早冒险登陆的动物之一
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.26,0:33:51.63,Chinese,,0,0,0,,感觉肯定像是造访另一个星球
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.13,0:33:55.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,森林  恐龙
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.53,0:33:57.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,鸟类 昆虫
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.87,0:34:01.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,都在12月的最后一周进化而来
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.27,0:34:03.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,,第一朵花
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.14,0:34:07.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在12月28号 盛开
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.85,0:34:13.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,随着古森林的成长死亡
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.62,0:34:15.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,并被深埋进地下
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.62,0:34:18.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们的残骸形成了煤
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.49,0:34:21.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,3亿年后
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.12,0:34:24.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,人类燃烧这些煤来推动文明的发展
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.46,0:34:27.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,同时也使我们的文明陷入危机
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.50,0:34:33.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,,还记得那颗在太阳系形成时的
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.90,0:34:35.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,小行星吗
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.57,0:34:37.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那颗被轻轻推动的小行星
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.74,0:34:40.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它来了
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.08,0:34:42.51,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}早晨6点24分
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.54,0:34:46.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}宇宙年历上的12月30号
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.86,0:34:55.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在1亿年的时间里
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.82,0:34:58.03,Chinese,,0,0,0,,恐龙曾是这个地球的统治者
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.06,0:35:00.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当我们的祖先 小型哺乳动物
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.83,0:35:02.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,战战兢兢地在地面爬来爬去的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.00,0:35:05.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这颗小行星改变了一切
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.40,0:35:07.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,假如它没有被推动
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.24,0:35:09.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它会完全和地球擦肩而过
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.07,0:35:11.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,恐龙恐怕依然存在
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.37,0:35:12.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但我们不会
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.01,0:35:15.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这是极端突发状况的好例子
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.01,0:35:18.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,,生存的偶然性
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.42,0:35:23.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}宇宙已经诞生了超过
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.72,0:35:25.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,135亿年
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.12,0:35:26.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,人类仍未出现
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.96,0:35:31.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在这个年历代表的时间长河中
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.13,0:35:34.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,人类在最后一小时进化
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.23,0:35:39.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,,宇宙年历中的最后一天
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.61,0:35:48.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}11点59分46秒
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.38,0:35:52.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,全部有记载的历史发生在最后的14秒里
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.61,0:35:55.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你听说过得所有人
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.38,0:35:57.39,Chinese,,0,0,0,,存在于这个点的某个位置
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.25,0:36:03.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所有这些国王 战役 迁徙 发明
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.23,0:36:07.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,战争和爱情 历史书中的一切
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.73,0:36:09.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,都发生在这宇宙年历中的最后几秒
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.80,0:36:11.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,,都发生在这宇宙年历中的最后几秒
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.90,0:36:14.07,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但如果我们想要研究
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.10,0:36:16.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,宇宙年历中这段极短的时间
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.27,0:36:21.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们必须改变比例
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.21,0:36:40.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们是这个宇宙的新丁
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.61,0:36:45.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们的历史仅仅从宇宙年的最后一晚开始
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.05,0:36:48.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,新年前夜的9点45分
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.45,0:36:50.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,350万年前
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.89,0:36:54.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你我的祖先留下这些足迹
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.16,0:36:59.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们站了起来和他们区别开来
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.83,0:37:01.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,自从我们直立行走
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.76,0:37:04.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们的双眼不在迷恋地面
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.93,0:37:08.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,,现在我们可以自由的探索奇迹
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.17,0:37:13.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,人类存在的大部分时间里
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.68,0:37:17.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,,比方说最近的4万代人
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.45,0:37:19.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们曾是流浪者
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.28,0:37:22.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,猎人和采集者混住在一起
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.48,0:37:25.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,制作工具 生火
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.15,0:37:27.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,给事物起名字
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.16,0:37:31.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,都发生在宇宙年历的最后一个小时里
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.63,0:37:43.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们必须改变比例去继续探寻
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.14,0:37:46.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,最后一晚的最后一分钟
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.34,0:37:49.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,发生了什么
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.38,0:37:51.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,11:59
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.38,0:37:54.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,以宇宙时间比例来说我们太太太年轻了
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.05,0:37:56.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们甚至还没开始画出第一张画
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.68,0:38:00.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,直到宇宙年历的最后60秒
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.29,0:38:03.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,,只不过是3万年前
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.03,0:38:14.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们发明了天文学
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.64,0:38:17.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}事实上我们都是天文学家的后裔
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.84,0:38:21.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们的生存要依靠研究星星
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.24,0:38:23.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}用来预测冬天的到来
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.58,0:38:26.18,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}以及兽群的迁徙
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.21,0:38:29.18,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}然后大约1万年前
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.22,0:38:32.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们的生活方式迎来了变革
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.22,0:38:35.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们的祖先学会了如何改变周围环境
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.49,0:38:37.86,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}栽培植物 驯养动物
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.89,0:38:40.86,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}耕作土地 定居下来
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.90,0:38:43.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这改变了一切
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.50,0:38:45.47,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}有史以来第一次
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.50,0:38:48.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们可以拥有超过我们负重能力的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.90,0:38:51.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们需要把这些数量记录下来
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.34,0:38:53.51,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}午夜前的14秒
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.54,0:38:57.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}大约6千年前 我们发明了书写
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.05,0:38:59.51,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}随后不久我们就开始记录其他东西
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.55,0:39:01.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}不仅仅是粮食的数量
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.28,0:39:03.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}书写让我们保存我们的想法
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.28,0:39:06.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}并且跨越时间和空间的传播它们
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.55,0:39:08.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}泥板上的细小印记
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.96,0:39:12.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}成了我们征服有限的生命的手段
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.23,0:39:15.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}震撼了整个世界
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.36,0:39:18.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}摩西出生于7秒之前
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.47,0:39:21.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}释迦摩尼 6秒前
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.40,0:39:24.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}耶稣基督 5秒前
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.31,0:39:27.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}穆罕穆德 3秒前
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.74,0:39:31.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}不到2秒前 不论好坏
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.15,0:39:34.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}地球一边的人类发现了地球的另一边
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.48,0:39:36.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}仅仅在最后的一秒钟里
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.75,0:39:39.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们开始使用科学
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.75,0:39:42.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}去揭示大自然的秘密和规则
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.92,0:39:45.63,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}科学方法是如此的强大
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.66,0:39:47.63,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}只用了4个世纪的时间
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.66,0:39:50.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}就从伽利略第一次看向望远镜
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.00,0:39:54.47,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}到人类在月球上留下足迹
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.50,0:39:58.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}它让我们可以越过时间和空间
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.01,0:40:04.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}去观察我们在宇宙时空中的位置
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.78,0:40:09.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们有了了解宇宙本质的办法
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.35,0:40:11.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,卡尔·萨根30多年前带领我们进行了首次的
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.69,0:40:13.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,宇宙航行
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.45,0:40:15.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他不仅是20世纪最成功的
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.66,0:40:17.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,科学传播者
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.16,0:40:19.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也是一位首屈一指的科学家
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.93,0:40:23.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}卡尔为我们了解行星
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.47,0:40:25.63,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}做出了极大的贡献
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.67,0:40:28.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他正确地预测了有沼气湖存在于
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.67,0:40:30.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}木星的卫星 泰坦 土卫六上
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.67,0:40:33.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他指出早期地球的大气层中
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.98,0:40:36.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1} 必然含有强大的温室气体
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.95,0:40:40.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他首先推断出火星上的季节变化
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.95,0:40:43.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}是由沙尘暴引起
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.45,0:40:44.99,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}卡尔是一位
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.02,0:40:46.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在探索地球以外智慧生物领域的
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.45,0:40:49.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}先行者
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.36,0:40:52.63,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}太空时代的最初40年里 每次主要的
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.66,0:40:55.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}太阳系探索航天任务 他都担任了
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.16,0:40:57.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}重要的职务
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.30,0:41:02.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这还不是全部
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.41,0:41:08.51,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这是卡尔的一本1975年的记事日历
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.48,0:41:13.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我那时在做什么
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.52,0:41:16.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我只是一个纽约的17岁男孩
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.35,0:41:18.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,梦想着可以成为科学家
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.75,0:41:22.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,,世界上最著名的天文学家
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.09,0:41:24.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,邀请我去纽约州
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.93,0:41:26.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,和他共度一个周六
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.73,0:41:30.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我记得那天下着雪
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.17,0:41:31.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他来公车站接我
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.00,0:41:34.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,,带我参观了他在康奈尔大学的实验室
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.90,0:41:39.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,卡尔从书桌后拿出这本书并在上面为我题字
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.08,0:41:45.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,,至 尼尔 未来的天文学家
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.78,0:41:47.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,卡尔
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.62,0:41:51.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,结束后 他开车送我去公车站
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.05,0:41:53.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,雪下得更大了
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.05,0:41:55.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他写下他的电话号码 家里的电话
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.06,0:41:58.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他把号码写在一张小纸片上 如果公车没有来
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.56,0:42:02.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,打电话给我 就在我家过夜
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.40,0:42:05.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我当时已经决定要当一名科学家
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.23,0:42:07.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是那天下午 我认识到
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.64,0:42:09.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我要做他那样的人
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.90,0:42:13.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他帮助了我 还有其他很多人
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.58,0:42:18.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,激励我们去学习，教授，研究科学
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.08,0:42:20.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,科学研究是一份需要合作的事业
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.48,0:42:22.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,持续几代人的时间
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.88,0:42:27.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,,火炬在老师和学生的手中传递
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.22,0:42:30.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一群伟大的思想从远古
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.73,0:42:32.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,贯穿 直至未来的星空
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.73,0:42:35.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,现在跟我来
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.56,0:42:38.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们的旅程开始了
